  "instructions": [
    "Prepare the tofu by cutting it into 1-inch cubes and coating with cornstarch.",
    "Heat 1/2 cup vegetable oil in a wok or large skillet over high heat.",
    "Double-fry the tofu in batches until golden brown and crispy, about 5 minutes per batch.",
    "Set the fried tofu aside on a paper towel-lined plate.",
    "In the same wok, add the remaining 1/2 cup vegetable oil, garlic, and green onions.",
    "Stir-fry for 1 minute until fragrant.",
    "Add the gochujang, gochugaru, treacle, and water to the wok, whisking to combine.",
    "Bring the mixture to a simmer and cook for 2-3 minutes until thickened.",
    "Add the cubed tofu, low-sodium soy sauce, and brown sugar to the wok.",
    "Stir-fry for 2 minutes to combine.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a serving dish and garnish with sesame seeds.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy!"
  ],
